<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="276" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1608,1959]" pageId="3" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1608,1634]" pageId="3" pageNumber="276">Notes:—</emphasis>
The new species belongs to the section VII of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ansari, R. &amp; Balakrishnan, N. P." box="[838,1200,1608,1634]" pageId="3" pageNumber="276" refId="ref2253" refString="Ansari, R. &amp; Balakrishnan, N. P. (1994) The family Eriocaulaceae in India. Bishen Singh Mahendra Pal Singh, Dehradun. 195 pp." type="book" year="1994">Ansari and Balakrishnan (1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ansari, R. &amp; Balakrishnan, N. P." box="[1214,1272,1608,1634]" pageId="3" pageNumber="276" refId="ref2284" refString="Ansari, R. &amp; Balakrishnan, N. P. (2009) The family Eriocaulaceae in India. Revised edition. Bishen Singh Mahendra Pal Singh, Dehradun. 188 pp." type="book" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
) in having free female sepals, black or dark brown anthers, and transversely elongated seed coat cells with ribbon like appendages on the surface of seeds. There are 13 species in this section from 
<collectingCountry box="[833,891,1680,1706]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="276">India</collectingCountry>
including the one described here. The differences between the morphologically most similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Ansari &amp; N. P. Balakrishnan" authorityYear="1994" box="[616,784,1716,1743]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="276" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ramnadense">
<emphasis box="[616,633,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="276">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[647,784,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="276">ramnadense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are given in diagnosis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1608,1959]" pageId="3" pageNumber="276">
It also differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Hooker (1893: 573)" authorityName="Hooker" authorityPageNumber="573" authorityYear="1893" box="[400,781,1752,1779]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="276" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longicuspis">
<emphasis box="[400,557,1752,1778]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="276">E. longicuspis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, J. D." box="[562,781,1752,1779]" pageId="3" pageNumber="276" refId="ref3322" refString="Hooker, J. D. (1893) Flora of British India. Vol. 6. L. Reeve &amp; Co., London, 578 pp." type="book" year="1893">Hooker (1893: 573)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by its elongated ribbon-like seed coat appendages and 3 subequal male petals, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[405,614,1788,1814]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="276" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quinquangulare">
<emphasis box="[405,614,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="276">E. quinquangulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fyson 1921: 260) C. E. C. Fischer (1931: 1620)" authorityName="C. E. C. Fischer" authorityPageNumber="1620" authorityYear="1931" baseAuthorityName="Fyson" baseAuthorityPageNumber="260" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[628,1286,1788,1815]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="276" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conicum">
<emphasis box="[628,754,1789,1814]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="276">E. conicum</emphasis>
